Aim:
To check if a number is an Armstrong number.

Algorithm:
Start
Input n
Make temp = n
Initialize sum = 0
While temp > 0
digit = temp % 10
sum += digit³
temp = temp / 10
If sum == n → Armstrong
Else → Not Armstrong
Stop

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int n, temp, sum = 0, digit;
    cout<<"Enter a number: ";
    cin>>n;
    temp = n;
    while(temp > 0){
        digit = temp % 10;
        sum += digit * digit * digit;
        temp /= 10;
    }
    if(sum == n)
        cout<<"Armstrong Number";
    else
        cout<<"Not Armstrong";
    return 0;
}

Sample Output:
Enter a number: 153
Armstrong Number

Result:
The program determines whether a number is Armstrong.
